\pard\f0\fs28\qc {\b  134.           MYRSINACEAE}
\par 

\pard\f0\fs24\qc Edit. †T.G. Tutin.
\par 

\par

\pard\f0\fs28 Shrubs or trees. Leaves alternate, simple, exstipulate. Flowers actinomorphic. Calyx 4- to 6-fid. Corolla usually sympetalous; lobes 4-6. Stamens equal in number to the corolla-lobes and opposite to them, epipetalous. Ovary superior, 1-locular. Fruit an indehiscent, dry or fleshy drupe.
\par 

