\pard\f0\fs28\qc {\b 1.             Myrsine}              L.
\par 

\pard\f0\fs24\qc By †T.G. Tutin.
\par 

\par

\pard\f0\fs28 Usually dioecious. Flowers in axillary fascicles. Calyx small, persistent. Corolla-lobes imbricate; tube usually very short. Fruit 1-seeded.
\par 

